data.description: Space. Solitude. Castle Mountain views. Income... This Chickaloon ''Financeable Fixer'' comes with not one but TWO adorable houses, nestled in the woods on 5 acres, a few hundred yards from all the trails up the Chick! Great property for a conventional loan, or call any Alaska real estate licensee for FHA/VA possibilities and to schedule a showing! Priced a whopping $30,000 below recent appraisalEach house is 2 bed / 1 bath, one built in 1974, the other in 2001. Both have a few outbuildings, including sheds and a barn, and each is tucked into its own little pocket in the woods with lots of privacy. The larger home, at 998 sq ft, features a walk-in pantry, generous foyer in addition to the living room, a cozy dining nook, decks in the front and back, arctic entry, and a full height basement. There large barn has plenty of room for lots of storage! These two little charmers are literally steps away from the end of the maintained road in Chickaloon, and the beginning of the trails that connect towards and up the Chickaloon River - worlds away from the highway just a short drive away! It's the Alaskan dream - living in the mountains at the end of the road, with views on every side and trails in every direction... with downtown Palmer only 40 minutes away. Multi-family options with income generation that are financeable are rare below $300k, much less with privacy and acreage. Come find it all in Chickaloon!
